Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: Dielectric spectroscopy was used to measure the real and imaginary permittivity. Samples were hot pressed into flat samples of ~300 m thickness. The measurements were carried out in a Novocontrol analyzer over a frequency range of 105 Hz to 10-1 Hz.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: SAXS was used to quantify the lamellar thickness, d-spacings of NPs in the crystallized matrix, and general NP morphology. A SAXSLAB Ganesha with q ranges ≈0.004-0.18 Å-1 was used. The SAXSLAB instrument used a Copper K-α X-ray source with a wavelength of 1.54 Å.
